<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Cybersecurity Dashboard</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.2/gsap.min.js"></script>
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
      background-color: #111827;
      color: #fff;
    }

    nav {
      background: #1f2937;
      padding: 1.5rem 3rem;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    }

    .nav-brand {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #60a5fa;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .nav-links a {
      color: #d1d5db;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-left: 2rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      transition: color 0.3s;
    }

    .nav-links a:hover {
      color: #60a5fa;
    }

    .cover-container {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100vh;
      background: url('https://via.placeholder.com/1920x1080?text=Cybersecurity+Cover+Image') no-repeat center center/cover;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      text-align: center;
      color: white;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .cover-cards {
      position: absolute;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      z-index: 0;
    }

    .cover-card {
      background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
      padding: 3rem;
      border-radius: 12px;
      margin: 0 1rem;
      box-shadow: 0 6px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
      transform: scale(0.9);
      opacity: 0;
      transition: transform 0.3s, opacity 0.5s;
    }

    .cover-content {
      max-width: 650px;
      padding: 3rem;
      background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
      border-radius: 15px;
      box-shadow: 0 6px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
      transform: translateY(100px);
      opacity: 0;
      transition: transform 0.5s, opacity 0.5s;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    .cover-content h1 {
      font-size: 3.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .cover-content p {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    .cta-button a {
      background: #60a5fa;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 1.2rem 2.5rem;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      transition: background 0.3s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    .cta-button a:hover {
      background: #1e293b;
      transform: translateY(-4px);
    }

    .attack-vectors {
      padding: 6rem 3rem;
      background: #1f2937;
      text-align: center;
      transition: background 0.3s;
    }

    .attack-vectors h2 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      color: #60a5fa;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .attack-vectors .vector {
      background-color: #334155;
      padding: 2rem;
      margin: 2rem 0;
      border-radius: 12px;
      box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
      transition: background 0.3s ease, transform 0.3s ease;
    }

    .attack-vectors .vector:hover {
      background-color: #1e293b;
      transform: translateY(-5px);
    }

    .attack-vectors .vector h3 {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .attack-vectors .vector p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: #d1d5db;
    }

  </style>
</head>
<body>

 <!-- ðŸ”— Navigation Bar -->
 <nav>
  <div class="nav-brand">CyberDash</div>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
    <a href="/card-checker">Card Checker</a>
    <a href="/services">Services</a>

    <!-- Conditionally display logout link -->
    <% if (!isLoggedIn) { %>
      <a href="/login">Login</a>
      <a href="/register">Register</a>
    <% } else { %>
      <a href="/logout">Logout</a>
    <% } %>
  </div>
</nav>

  <!-- Cover Container with Eye-Catching Message and Card Stacking -->
  <div class="cover-container">
    <div class="cover-cards">
      <div class="cover-card"></div>
      <div class="cover-card"></div>
      <div class="cover-card"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-content">
      <h1> Secure Your Digital Life with CyberDash</h1>
      <p>Join us in defending your online presence. Our cutting-edge security solutions protect your personal data and help you stay one step ahead of cybercriminals.</p>
      <div class="cta-button">
        <a href="/services">Explore Our Plans</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Common Attack Vectors Section -->
  <div class="attack-vectors">
    <h2> Common Cyber Attack Vectors </h2>

    <div class="vector">
      <h3>Phishing Attacks</h3>
      <p>Phishing attacks involve deceptive emails or websites that impersonate legitimate sources. These attacks aim to steal sensitive information such as login credentials, banking details, and personal data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="vector">
      <h3>Ransomware</h3>
      <p>Ransomware encrypts the victimâ€™s files, locking them out of access. Cybercriminals demand a ransom payment in exchange for the decryption key, often leading to large financial losses.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="vector">
      <h3>SQL Injection</h3>
      <p>SQL injection is a malicious technique used to manipulate a website's database. Attackers exploit vulnerabilities in web applications, gaining access to confidential data stored in SQL databases.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="vector">
      <h3>Man-in-the-Middle (MitM) Attacks</h3>
      <p>In MitM attacks, hackers intercept and alter communication between two parties. They can steal data, inject malicious content, or manipulate transactions, often targeting unsecured networks.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="vector">
      <h3>Malware</h3>
      <p>Malware is a broad term for any malicious software designed to damage, disrupt, or gain unauthorized access to systems. It can take many forms, including viruses, worms, and trojans.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- ðŸŒŸ GSAP Animation for Cover Content and Card Stacking -->
  <script>
    // GSAP Animation for Cover Content
    gsap.to(".cover-content", { duration: 1.5, opacity: 1, y: 0, ease: "power2.out" });

    // GSAP Animation for Card Stacking
    gsap.from(".cover-card", {
      duration: 1.5,
      opacity: 0,
      y: -30,
      scale: 0.8,
      stagger: 0.2,
      ease: "power2.out",
    });

    // GSAP Animation for Attack Vectors
    gsap.from(".vector", { duration: 1, opacity: 0, y: 30, ease: "power2.out", stagger: 0.3 });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
